Active Side Collision Avoidance Support - Volvo Dynamic Steering with Lane Keeping Assist","comments":"<p>The Volvo FH rigid was rated as a partner to the FH tractor and the results verified very similar performance between the vehicles. The FH is an excellent choice for a safe vehicle in the fleet long haul sector. Its direct vision is good for a tall cab, helped by the optional fit camera monitoring system. Combined with very good assistance systems, some of which are optional, they produce a good Safe Driving score. It achieves a very good score in Collision Avoidance, with every system Euro NCAP assess being available including automated braking to protect a cyclist where the truck turns across their path. As a highway truck, its good direct vision combined with very good AEB for vulnerable road users also earns the Volvo FH our CitySafe award alongside its 5 stars. It is an excellent choice for long haul operations that require occasional city deliveries, provided all the options are selected at purchase.</p><p>The Volvo FH has a very good Safe Driving performance. It is a tall truck which limits vision but this is mitigated by good window design and the optional camera monitor system to replace conventional class II/IV mirrors. An optional class V camera monitor system is available, which brings up a view of the nearside blind spot on a secondary monitor, whenever the direction indicators are activated. This improves the vision at the front corner, but duplicating the conventional mirror risks an increase in driver workload. Seat belt reminders are fitted to all seats, encouraging belt use. The attention assist system exceeds minimum legal requirements without excessive false alerts. A close following distance warning is available and the use of the ACC reduces the risk of front to rear collisions.</p><p>The Volvo FH is equipped with class leading collision avoidance technology. It is equipped with an AEB system that avoids front to rear collisions with vehicles ahead in nearly every circumstance that Euro NCAP assess. It is also very good at avoiding frontal collisions with pedestrians and cyclists. Volvo is one of the few truck manufacturers to offer a system that  automatically brakes to protect cyclists if the truck turns to the nearside across their path. A requirement Euro NCAP see as necessary for safe city operations. An optional lane support system is available, which performs exceptionally well, fulfilling nearly all of Euro NCAP’s requirements.</p>","testedHandOfDrive":null,"assessmentTags":[{"code":"ELECTRIC","name":"Electric"},{"code":"CITY_SAFE","name":"City Safe"}],"assessmentData":{"truckSafety":{"nicePublicationDate":"February 2026","safetyPerformance":{"starRating":5,"safeDriving":{"normalisedScore":77,"occupantMonitoring":{"score":25,"maxScore":25,"seatbeltUsage":{"score":15,"maxScore":15,"verdict":"GREEN"},"driverMonitoring":{"score":10,"maxScore":10,"verdict":"GREEN"}},"vision":{"score":28.3,"maxScore":50,"directVision":{"score":18.7,"maxScore":35,"verdict":"YELLOW","result":{"volume":9.9,"unit":"M3"}},"indirectVision":{"score":9.5,"maxScore":15,"verdict":"YELLOW"}},"vehicleAssistance":{"score":24.3,"maxScore":25,"speedAssistance":{"score":14.4,"maxScore":15,"verdict":"GREEN"},"adaptiveCruiseControlPerformance":{"score":9.9,"maxScore":10,"verdict":"GREEN"}}},"crashAvoidance":{"normalisedScore":85,"frontalCollisions":{"score":56.3,"maxScore":60,"car":{"score":34.7,"maxScore":35,"verdict":"GREEN"},"pedestrianAndCyclist":{"score":21.6,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"GREEN"}},"laneDepartureCollisions":{"score":23.4,"maxScore":25,"laneDeparture":{"score":13.4,"maxScore":15,"verdict":"GREEN"},"car":{"score":10,"maxScore":10,"verdict":"GREEN"}},"lowSpeedManoeuvringCollisions":{"score":5,"maxScore":15,"turnAcrossPathCyclist":{"score":5,"maxScore":15,"verdict":"ORANGE"}}},"postCrashSafety":{"normalisedScore":80,"rescueInformation":{"score":80,"maxScore":90,"rescueSheet":{"score":80,"maxScore":80,"verdict":"GREEN"},"